						               													<description>SOUTHERN OKINAWA: DAWN, 9 APRIL, 1945&amp;#10;The American 383rd Infantry Regiment has successfully infiltrated Kakazu Ridge and holds the crest, catching the Japanese completely by surprise.  But the men of the 13th Independent Battalion won&amp;rsquo;t let go of the ridge without a fight.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this mini-campaign, command either beleaguered American infantry, under constant attack and cut off from their heavy artillery, or lead Japanese troops in ferocious attacks up the slopes of Kakazu Ridge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Historically, the American companies were decimated and thrown back, but not without mauling the Japanese battalion that faced them.  How will you fare?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Kakazu Ridge is a 3-scenario mini-campaign portraying small-unit infantry combat during the Battle of Okinawa.  It has been written for A Sergeant&amp;rsquo;s War, but can easily be adapted to other WWII rules sets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The campaign includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Historical background, with maps and contemporary pictures&amp;#10;     Campaign special rules&amp;#10;     3 linked scenarios, with overall victory determined by holding terrain, overrunning the enemy, and inflicting casualties&amp;#10;     A painting tutorial for 15mm Japanese infantry&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
